  "prompt": "How many rounds of admission will be conducted for an MBA at NIT Trichy?",
  "response": "NIT Trichy usually conducts multiple rounds of admission for its MBA program. These typically include:\n\n1. **Shortlisting of candidates**: Based on CAT scores.\n2. **Group Discussion (GD)**: Shortlisted candidates participate in GD sessions.\n3. **Personal Interview (PI)**: Candidates who clear the GD round are called for PI.\n\nThese rounds ensure a comprehensive evaluation of candidates. The exact number of rounds can vary each year, and additional rounds like a Written Ability Test (WAT) might be included. It's best to check the specific year\u2019s admission guidelines on the official NIT Trichy website or contact their admission office directly for the most accurate information.",
